      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Reject unsupported diagnostics OTel grpc config",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #93069.\n\nThis keeps the config contract honest without stranding existing configs:\n\n- `diagnostics.otel.protocol` now documents and validates the only implemented transport: `http/protobuf`.\n- Existing shipped configs with `diagnostics.otel.protocol: \"grpc\"` are now handled by `openclaw doctor --fix` instead of simply becoming invalid on upgrade.\n- If the old config also had telemetry enabled, doctor disables `diagnostics.otel.enabled` while removing `protocol`, preserving the old runtime behavior where `grpc` never exported telemetry.\n- `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_PROTOCOL=grpc` remains a fail-closed runtime override path, and now has focused regression coverage.\n- Real gRPC exporter support is intentionally out of scope here.\n\n## Linked context\n\nCloses #93069.\n\nRelated review concern: ClawSweeper flagged the first version because it rejected a shipped config value without an upgrade path. This revision adds that doctor migration path and proof.\n\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: Existing `diagnostics.otel.protocol: \"grpc\"` configs no longer get stranded by the stricter schema; doctor removes the unsupported protocol and disables enabled telemetry until the operator chooses an OTLP/HTTP collector.\n- Real environment tested: Local OpenClaw source checkout on macOS, Node v25.6.1, branch head `074f6a0b45`.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```bash\nnode --import tsx --input-type=module -e '\n  const { validateConfigObjectRaw } = await import(\"./src/config/validation.ts\");\n  const { migrateLegacyConfig } = await import(\"./src/commands/doctor/shared/legacy-config-migrate.ts\");\n  const input = { diagnostics: { otel: { enabled: true, endpoint: \"http://otel-collector:4317\", protocol: \"grpc\" } } };\n  const before = validateConfigObjectRaw(input);\n  const migrated = migrateLegacyConfig(input);\n  const after = validateConfigObjectRaw(migrated.config ?? {});\n  console.log(\"before.ok=\" + before.ok);\n  if (!before.ok) console.log(\"before.issue=\" + before.issues.find((issue) => issue.path === \"diagnostics.otel.protocol\")?.message);\n  console.log(\"migration.changes=\" + JSON.stringify(migrated.changes));\n  console.log(\"after.config=\" + JSON.stringify(migrated.config?.diagnostics?.otel));\n  console.log(\"after.ok=\" + after.ok);\n'\n```\n\n- Evidence after fix (screenshot, recording, terminal capture, console output, redacted runtime log, linked artifact, or copied live output):\n\n```text\nbefore.ok=false\nbefore.issue=Invalid input: expected \"http/protobuf\" (allowed: \"http/protobuf\")\nmigration.changes=[\"Removed unsupported diagnostics.otel.protocol \\\"grpc\\\"; use \\\"http/protobuf\\\" with an OTLP/HTTP collector.\",\"Disabled diagnostics.otel.enabled because legacy grpc configs never exported telemetry; re-enable it after choosing an OTLP/HTTP collector.\"]\nafter.config={\"enabled\":false,\"endpoint\":\"http://otel-collector:4317\"}\nafter.ok=true\n```\n\n- Observed result after fix: The unsupported `grpc` config is rejected by validation before migration, doctor migration removes `protocol`, disables enabled telemetry, keeps the endpoint intact, and the migrated config validates successfully.\n- What was not tested: A live OTLP collector or real telemetry export; real gRPC exporter support is not implemented by this PR.\n- Proof limitations or environment constraints: The direct proof imports the actual config validation and doctor migration modules from the source checkout. The runtime env override path is covered by the focused diagnostics-otel service test below rather than by a live collector run.\n- Before evidence (optional but encouraged): ClawSweeper’s earlier review reproduced the issue by source inspection and flagged the lack of a doctor/migration path for shipped `grpc` configs.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/commands/doctor/shared/legacy-config-migrate.test.ts src/commands/doctor/shared/deprecation-compat.test.ts src/commands/doctor-config-preflight.test.ts src/commands/doctor-config-flow.test.ts src/commands/doctor-config-flow.test-utils.ts src/config/validation.allowed-values.test.ts src/config/schema.help.quality.test.ts src/config/schema.test.ts extensions/diagnostics-otel/src/service.test.ts`\n  - Passed: 5 Vitest shards, 343 tests.\n- `git diff --check`\n  - Passed.\n\nRegression coverage added:\n\n- Doctor migration removes `diagnostics.otel.protocol: \"grpc\"` and disables enabled telemetry.\n- Doctor preflight reports shipped `grpc` configs as repairable legacy config.\n- Doctor config flow applies the repair end to end.\n- Config validation reports the allowed value as `http/protobuf`.\n- Diagnostics OTel service rejects `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_PROTOCOL=grpc` before exporter startup.\n- Deprecation compatibility inventory tracks the migration so it is not deleted accidentally.\n\n## Risk checklist\n\nDid user-visible behavior change? `Yes` — unsupported `grpc` config now fails validation, with doctor repair for existing configs.\n\nDid config, environment, or migration behavior change? `Yes` — schema narrows to `http/protobuf`, and doctor migrates legacy `grpc` configs.\n\nDid security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? `No`.\n\nHighest-risk area: upgrade behavior for existing `diagnostics.otel.protocol: \"grpc\"` configs. The doctor migration is intentionally conservative: it preserves the old no-export outcome by disabling telemetry when the unsupported `grpc` config had been enabled.\n",
